ce it.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n\n    <a class=\"ebook-banner ebook-banner--sl\" href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/shop\/ebooks\/sri-lanka\/\" target=\"_blank\">\n        <img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" data-src=\"\/build\/images\/ebooks\/traveling-sri-lanka\/slebook-banner.jpg\" class=\"lazypreload\" height=\"225\" width=\"800\" alt=\"Ebook Sri Lanka\">\n    <\/a>\n    \n\n\n\n<p>The train was brought to life in the mid-1800s when <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/sri-lanka\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Sri Lanka<\/a> was under British colonial rule. During this time, it was used as a train to transport tea from the plantations to Colombo, where it would then be exported internationally. These days, it&#x2019;s used mainly by locals who use it to travel between home and work. Because of this, getting a ticket as a tourist can be a little more difficult, as seats sell out fast.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18222324\/train-sri-lanka-1-1080x720.jpg\" alt=\"Kandy Ella train sri lanka\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"300\" alt=\"Kandy Ella train sri lanka\" class=\"wp-image-73797 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18222324\/train-sri-lanka-1-1080x720.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18222324\/train-sri-lanka-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18222324\/train-sri-lanka-1-450x300.jpg 450w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18222324\/train-sri-lanka-1-30x20.jpg 30w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18222324\/train-sri-lanka-1-163x109.jpg 163w, http